# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
This problem is a variation of 2Sum and especially 3Sum problem. In 3Sum, we choose a triplet and checks its sum equal to 0(target). here we have to find the sum of triplet closest to target. so use the same approach as we have used in 3Sum problem.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
first thing is to think how you can get closest sum. For this sort the vector for easiness. 
if sum is greater then target, but we need sum closest, that is ,**the minimum sum greater than equal to target** declare min1 variable with **min1 = INT_MAX - 10000;** we did -10000 so that we can get rid of TLE.  and same for when sum is smaller than target , that is, **the greatest sum smaller than equal to target** for this declare, **max1 = INT_MIN + 10000** . if sum is equal to target return the sum. 

now the question is which variale min1, max1 we have to return, for this, find the absolute difference of min1, max1 with target and return min1 or max1 as per the minimum diff obtained.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n2)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int threeSumClosest(vector<int>& nums, int target) 
    {
        int  n= nums.size();
        int sum=0, j=0,k=0;
        int max1 = INT_MIN + 10000, min1 = INT_MAX - 10000;
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        for(int i=0; i< (n-2); i++)
        {
            j= i+1;
            k= n-1;
            while(j < k)
            {
                sum= nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k];

                if(sum == target)
                    return sum;

                else if(sum>target)
                {
                    min1= min(min1, sum);
                    k--;
                }
                else if(sum < target)
                {
                    max1= max( max1, sum);
                    j++;
                }
            }
        }
        // target =10, a=2, b=1;

        int a= min1 - target;
        int b= target - max1;

        if(a < b)
        return min1;
        else
        return max1;
    }
};
```

