## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- A basic approach using 3loops.
- We calculate the sum of 3 elements & store the difference of sum and target.
- If the difference is less than the minimum value we expected, then we’ll store the sum as ans.
- **Time complexity:** O(n^3).

### Solution 02

- Here we sort the array & will use 2 pointers to get the sum.
- Fix an index ***i*** & ***left=i+1, right=n-1.***
- If the sum of the 3 elements is less than the target, then we’ll shift the left pointer which will increase the value.
- Else we will shift right to decrease sum value.
- Also, we’ll calculate the difference and store in ***mn*** & update ***ans.***
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
**class Solution {
public:
    int threeSumClosest(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        int n=nums.size();
        int sum, diff, ans, i=0, j=0, k=0, x=INT_MAX;
        while(i<n-2){
            sum = nums[i];
            j=i+1;
            while(j<n-1){
                sum += nums[j];
                k=j+1;
                while(k<n){
                    sum += nums[k];
                    diff = abs(target-sum);
                    if(diff<x){
                        x = diff;
                        ans = sum;
                    }
                    sum -= nums[k];
                    k++;
                }
                sum -= nums[j];
                j++;
            }i++;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};**

