solutions.content:
Observation : The tree is **Perfect**. This means all nodes have 2 childs or no childs, across the tree. 
We will use this observation to make changes to **next** based on state of the node itself or both its children

```
class Solution {
    public Node connect(Node root) {

		// In case the node itself is null, or any of its children are null we return the root. Both childs are null when we reach the leaf node 
        if(root ==null || root.left == null || root.right == null) {
            return root;
        }

		// The left child will always point to the right child
        root.left.next = root.right;

		// If the node has a right sibling on same level, then node's right child should always point to the sibling's left child and so on across the level
        if(root.next != null) {
            root.right.next = root.next.left;
        }

		// We call the function recursively on both left and right children so that the same operations are performed at each level
        connect(root.left); 
        connect(root.right);

		// Returning the root for the modified sub-tree/tree
        return root;
    }
}
```

