Algorithm:
1. We have to travel all cells by recursion
2. If the node is null then we return, that will be the base case.
2. Then we will check if the node have a parent or not, if it doesn't have parent then we know it is root and the next will be null
3. Then we check if it is left or right
4. If it is left then the next will be the parent's right
5. If it is right then we check if parent's next is null or not if it is null then it is means it is the rightmost then it's next will also be null
6. And if the parent's next is not null then the next will be paren't next left.

```
class Solution {
    public Node connect(Node root) {
        util(null, root, true);
        return root;
    }

    public void util(Node parent, Node node, boolean isLeft) {
        if (node == null) return;
		if (parent == null) node.next = null;
        else {
            if(isLeft)  node.next = parent.right;
            else  node.next = parent.next == null ? null : parent.next.left;
        }
        util(node, node.left, true);
        util(node, node.right, false);
    }
}
```

