# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For every combination we try out, we get an option of either selecting a digit from 1 to 9, or rejecting it and moving to the next one. Once we've made that choice, we have to continue making that decision for digits succeeding the current one.

This process is repeated till we either run out of the number of digits we can select, or the current sum becomes equal to the required sum.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Declare a function `generateCombos` with the parameters `idx` that indicates the number current number whose selection/rejection is to be decided, `k` that represents the number of digits we can select, `n` that represents the required sum, `temp` that stores the possible combination generated and `sol` that contains all possible solutions.

Iterate from `idx` to 9, selecting/rejecting values to be added to the possible solution. If the value to be selected is greater than the required sum `n`, return to the function call.

In all other cases, select the current value and recursively call the function with the next digit and the new, reduced values of `k` and `n`. Finally, reject the current value and move on the the subsequent values to generate all possible subcases.

If at any point in the function calls the number of moves become zero and the required sum is obtained, push it into the `sol` solution vector.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(k*9^k)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(k)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    void generateCombos(int idx, int k, int n, vector<int>& temp, vector<vector<int>>& sol){
        if(!k||!n){
            if(!k&&!n) sol.push_back(temp);
            return;
        }

        for(int i=idx;i<=9;i++){
            if(n<i) return;

            temp.push_back(i);
            generateCombos(i+1, k-1, n-i, temp, sol);
            temp.pop_back();
        }
    }

    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum3(int k, int n) {
        vector<int> temp;
        vector<vector<int>> sol;

        generateCombos(1, k, n, temp, sol);
        return sol;
    }
};
```

