**If (n > 45)** : Suppose, we take k (*i.e. no of numbers*)  = 9 (*k's max value*) and we are allowed to take one occurence of each number, then the maximum sum will 45. So, in any case, if n is given greater than 45, then it is not possible to give any answer.

-----------------------------

**Variables used :**
```vector<vector<int>> res;```            : to store the result whose sum will be equal to n
```vector<int> temp;```                       : to store every value on which we are iterating and comparing the sum with n
```int index = 0;```                               : to keep a check on the index of array arr[ ]
```int arr[9] = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9};```  : To iterate on the values

-----------------------------

**picknotpick( ) function :** 
Example : k = 3 , n = 7 || Answer : [ [ 1, 2, 4 ] ]

There are two aspects. To choose that element or not to choose that element. And we are taking considering both the situations. 
This code is choosing / picking up the element.
```
temp.push_back(arr[index]);
sum += arr[index];
picknotpick(arr, res, temp, k, n, index + 1, sum);
```
Below, three lines of code are not choosing the element and skipping it.
```
temp.pop_back();
sum -= arr[index];
picknotpick(arr, res, temp, k, n, index + 1, sum);
```
-----------------------
```if(index == 9) return;``` : is used to stop *index + 1* called in the functions throwing exception index out of bound.

---------------------------

**Complete code :**

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum3(int k, int n) {
        if(n > 45) return {};

        vector<vector<int>> res;
        vector<int> temp;
        int index = 0;
        int arr[9] = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9};
        picknotpick(arr, res, temp, k, n, index, 0);
        return res;
    }
    void picknotpick(int arr[], vector<vector<int>> &res, vector<int> temp, int k, int n, int index, int sum)
    {
        if(temp.size() == k)
        {
            if(sum == n) res.push_back(temp);
            return;
        }
        if(index == 9) return;
        temp.push_back(arr[index]);
        sum += arr[index];
        picknotpick(arr, res, temp, k, n, index + 1, sum);

        temp.pop_back();
        sum -= arr[index];
        picknotpick(arr, res, temp, k, n, index + 1, sum);
    }
};
```

