[1673. Find the Most Competitive Subsequence](https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-most-competitive-subsequence/)

* here in this question we need k elements
* then while processing current element we need to check two main conditions i.e is there any index before , which contains value greater than present and another condition is can we satisfy k elements conditon if we remove last element from result
* we need minimum number at minimum-index-possible to make it more competetive

```
    vector<int> mostCompetitive(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> ans;
        int n = nums.size();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        while(!ans.empty() && (ans.back()>nums[i]) && (n+ans.size()-i>k))
          ans.pop_back();
          if(k>ans.size()) ans.push_back(nums[i]);
        }

        return ans;
    }
