# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We will here see if there is any character bigger than current character than we will see if it is occuring agina or not . 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Count the occurrences of each character in the string and store the counts in an array.
2. Iterate through each character in the string:
Decrement the count for the current character.
-If the character is already in charset, skip it.
-If the character is smaller than the top of the stack, pop characters from the stack until a smaller character is encountered or the stack is empty.
-Add the current character to charset and push it onto the stack.
3. At last we will construct the result by poping the stack element and adding it to result string.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(n)
